                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that 450,000,000 taels and 4 per cent bonds at par may be
                    considered as the indemnity agreed upon. Japan can only borrow at 5 per cent,
                    and will consequently lose heavily at that rate. She submits the difficulty of
                    her position. Asks if Mr. Hay can suggest a way of securing her against loss.
                    The same question has been telegraphed by the British and German ministers to
                    their Governments. Prospects for early termination of negotiations are
                    favorable.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
